ENTRY            D1087   20260302   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D1087001   20260302   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 13         23
TITLE      Excitation functions for proton nuclear reactions on
            64Zn, 66Zn, and 68Zn by stacked foil method
AUTHOR     (H.-S.Jin, H.Kim, Y.-S.Jong)
INSTITUTE  (3KDRKDR) Kim Il Sung University, Pyongyang
REFERENCE  (J,IJP,99,2611,2025)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3KDRPYN) MGC-20 cyclotron of Institute of Atomic
            Energy, Pyongyang
SAMPLE     The target consisted of 17 zinc foils (18-20 mg/cm2)
            and 18 copper foils (21.38 mg/cm2), each >99.99% pure
            and the foils were stacked one Cu foil by one Zn foil.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) 100 cm3
MONITOR    (29-CU-63(P,N)30-ZN-63,,SIG)
           (29-CU-65(P,N)30-ZN-65,,SIG)
DECAY-MON  (30-ZN-63,38.1MIN,DG,670.,0.084,
                             DG,962.,0.066)
           (30-ZN-65,243.2D,DG,1116.,0.507)
METHOD     (ACTIV,BCINT) A Faraday cup with a current integrator
            measured the 18 MeV proton beam flux over 15 min,
            yielding a total integrated charge of 6.0210E-05 C.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The errors are below 20% for most data in
            the 3-18 MeV energy range.
STATUS     (TABLE,,H.-S.Jin+,J,IJP,99,2611,2025) Table 2
HISTORY    (20260302C) VT
ENDBIB              23
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           26
SUBENT        D1087002   20260302   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                  5         11
REACTION   (30-ZN-66(P,N)31-GA-66,,SIG,,,DERIV)
DECAY-DATA (31-GA-66,9.4HR,DG,834.,0.061,
                           DG,1039.,0.384)
SAMPLE     (30-ZN-66,NAT=0.279)
ANALYSIS   The contribution of 67Zn(p,2n)66Ga was subtracted.
            The corresponding cross section was estimated using
            previously published studies.
REL-REF    (R,D4004001,F.Tarkanyi+,J,RCA,50,19,1990)
           (R,A0510001,V.N.Levkovski,B,LEVKOVSKIJ,,,1991)
           These references were used to estimate the
            67Zn(p,2n)66Ga cross section.
ENDBIB              11
